SIMPLE: oneself
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Oneself
<hw>One`self"</hw> <pr>(w⟦ucr⟧n`s⟦ecr⟧lf")</pr>, <pos>pron.</pos> <def>A
reflexive form of the indefinite pronoun <xex>one</xex>. Commonly
written as two words, <xex>one's self</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>One's self (or more properly <qex>oneself</qex>), is quite a
modern form. In Elizabethan English we find <qex>a man's self = one's
self</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Morris.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>one-seventh</ent>⟦br⟧
